{
  "texts": [
    "The green numbers show the numbering of the strands, given by choosing a numbering near a basepoint b and continuing it compatibly in clockwise direction.",
    "The matrices are the partial formal monodromies given by the transformation rule (they come from the formal monodromies on the left, but change signs whenever one transits from a positive to a negative strand).",
    "identifies the sectors on both sides, and the algorithm gives us the induced transition maps defining the formal monodromy of the new formal local system, as indicated in Figure 11: If we choose a basepoint and an ordering of the strands, we get three transition matrices (in blue) for the formal local system of the Fourier transform (considered as a rank 2 local system on the boundary circle), the third one taking into account the twist (permutation of the strands).",
    "There are three Stokes arrows in the Airy case (i.e.",
    "in the picture after Fourier transform)."
  ]
}